"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1054604","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>Egypt is a Foreign and Commonwealth Office Human Rights Priority Country and the UK continues to urge the Egyptian Government to ensure full implementation of the rights and freedoms set out in Egypt's Constitution. We regularly raise concerns about human rights with the Egyptian Government both in public and in private. I raised our human rights concerns with the Egyptian Foreign Minister during my visit to Cairo on 14 October 2018.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2019-02-12T15:55:53.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1054604/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1054604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1054604/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-02-04","Egypt: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his counterpart in Egypt on the maintenance of human rights in Egypt.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","216260"
