"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052504","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-08","<p>As part of the Department’s ‘no deal’ European Union exit contingency planning contract agreements have been signed for the provision of storage. The contracts include capacity for 5,000 pallets of refrigerated warehouse storage.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2019-02-08T12:50:15.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052504/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1052504/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-01","NHS: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 11 January 2019 to Question 205244 on Drugs: Refrigerators, how many refrigerators his Department has purchased as part of contingency planning for the UK leaving the EU to date.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","215569"
